         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 24 March 1892. ¶ T. R. Wilson Esqr ¶ Under Secretary. ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.03.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">U92/3565, unit 667, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24 March 1892.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Under Secretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to report, that I have just learned, that the vacancy in the Forest-Department will be filled up within that establishment, so that the candidature of Mr Renner for that position has lapsed. May I therefore solicit, that he, through the kindness of the hon the Chief Secretary, participate in the favor, shown to Mr Minchin and Mr French, to remain during the next quarter in the Gov. Botanists Establishment, so long til a position can be found for him.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When the decision was made to abolish the post of Government Botanist from 31 March 1892, M was required to serve written notice on all his staff that their employment would cease on that date (T. Wilson to M, 15 January 1892). There was much opposition to the decision to retire M<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(see, for example, notes to M to T. Wilson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>23 January 1892),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and the decision was rescinded<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but with a reduced vote meaning that M would need to reduce staff. His decision to retain the highest paid staff member, G. Leuhmann, meant that he had to lose some junior staff (M to T. Wilson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>31 January 1892). Various positions were proposed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for Renner<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and he was eventually transferred to the Forest Branch of the Mines Department (M to T. Wilson, 31 March 1892<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 92-03-31b), but<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was returned to M's department the following year (M to G. Bell,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>24 June 1893<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 93-06-24b))<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>though<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>without the quarters he had previously had (M to T. Wilson, 23 September 1893<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 93-09-23b)). He was transferred again to the Government Statist (T. Wilson to M, 27 February 1894<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 94-02-27a)).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sir, your obedient servant</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>Gov. Botanist.</p>
         </div>
